Please give this AMAZING place your business!  Friends from Seattle surprised me with a visit on Saturday evening.   Their only NOLA request was to find a bar for the Seahawks' game.  Unfortunately, they were playing at SAME time as Saints, so their request seemed impossible.  I messaged American Sports Saloon 18 hours before the games, not expecting a response.  But I got an immediate reply with specific personalized instruction for reservations.  BEST customer service EVER in NOLA.  We were seated in a room with other Seahawks fans & had such a wonderful experience--my friends even saw other fans they knew from Seattle!  Greatest night ever thanks to American Sports Saloon!

We went here for the Patriots game while staying in New Orleans this past weekend.  The good part was that we had a separate room with multiple TV’s with the sound on for the Pats game and probably 40 or so other Pats fans to watch the game with.  The bar staff was very friendly, the beer was cold and the food, although we didn’t eat, looked very good when we saw it being delivered to others.  The bad part, the A/C in this bar is terrible and it was VERY hot in there!!  At game time, the temp on the control said 86!!  Ugh!!  They also had issues with their DirectTV connection and lost the broadcast multiple times throughout the game even though there were no storms in the area.  Overall, it was a good place but most likely would go somewhere else to watch the game if we are ever back in town for a Patriots Sunday.

Here’s my experience if I could put a lower rating I would. Me and my girlfriend visited during the cowboys vs Seahawks game back in January. Our tab was $82.30 i had opened with my credit card. When I was brought my receipt to close out I told our waiter not to charge card I was going to pay out with cash. I gave him $100 dollars and said no change. He did a great job. Next morning when I checked my account I had a pending charge from the American sports saloon. Thinking there had been some kind of mistake I called them and spoke with a manager who assured me that the charge would not go thru. That there system would hold charge but would go thru since I had paid the tab with cash. Sure enough that Monday my card was charged the $82.30. When I called back again and spoke with a employee he took my information and said he would pass my Information to manager and have them look into it and that they would get back to me. A few days passed and heard nothing so I called again. When I got the manager on the phone I had to explain my whole situation again because he had no idea who I was or was aware of my situation. At this point I requested to speak to the owner. After a few days I was contacted the owner Jim via phone and explained everything. He was very friendly and understanding we exchanged information and emails and he reassured me that he would personally write me a check for reimbursement and apologized for any inconvenience. It is now April 4th as I type this and have yet to receive a check or hear any response from the owner or management. I have contacted New Orleans PD and have opened a case. So for all those looking to enjoy a sports bar in the heart of the French quarter. I would strongly advise to seek elsewhere because I wish I had. You have been warned.
